tracks.fmtDetailValue_Dbxref: function(dbxref){ var items = []; var output = 'N/A'; var isArray; if(dbxref.constructor === Array){ for(i = 0; i < dbxref.length; i++){ ref = dbxref[i].split(':'); if(ref[0] == "GeneID"){ items.push('Entrez Gene: ' + ref[1] + ''); } else if(ref[0] == "Xenbase"){ items.push('Xenbase Gene Page'); } else if(ref[0] == "Genbank"){ items.push('Genbank');}}} else{ ref = dbxref.split(':'); if(ref[0] == "GeneID"){ items.push('Entrez Gene: ' + ref[1] + ''); } else if(ref[0] == "Xenbase"){ items.push('Xenbase Gene Page'); } else if(ref[0] == "Genbank"){ items.push('Genbank');}} if(items.length != 0){ output = items.join(", ");} return output;}

tracks.key: Transcription factor binding sites
tracks.label: TFBSv1_0

metadata.Info:
The putative transcription factor binding sites are identified by running fimo on X. laevis 9.2 genome
using motifs downloaded from CIS-BP database, and filtered by the peaks of epigenetic data,
including H3K4me1, H3K4me3, P300 at stage 10.5.

tracks.key: Pseudogenes
tracks.label: hybrid_pseudo

metadata.Info:
This pseudogene track includes both processed pseudogenes (colored green)
and NCBI pseudogenes (colored yellow). The processed pseudogenes are
generated by aligning protein sequences to genome sequences,
merging adjacent homologies, and realigning protein sequences
to genome sequences using fasta. The method was presented
in two papers by Zhang et al (2002 and 2003).

tracks.fmtDetailValue_Dbxref: function(dbxref){ var items = []; var output = 'N/A'; var isArray; if(dbxref.constructor === Array){ for(i = 0; i < dbxref.length; i++){ ref = dbxref[i].split(':'); if(ref[0] == "GeneID"){ items.push('Entrez Gene: ' + ref[1] + ''); } else if(ref[0] == "Xenbase"){ items.push('Xenbase Gene Page'); } else if(ref[0] == "Genbank"){ items.push('Genbank');}}} else{ ref = dbxref.split(':'); if(ref[0] == "GeneID"){ items.push('Entrez Gene: ' + ref[1] + ''); } else if(ref[0] == "Xenbase"){ items.push('Xenbase Gene Page'); } else if(ref[0] == "Genbank"){ items.push('Genbank');}} if(items.length != 0){ output = items.join(", ");} return output;}
